<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-820] SegmentReader.setNorm can fail to remove separate norms file, on Windows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-820</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>
&lt;p&gt;While working through &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-710&quot; title=&quot;Implement &amp;quot;point in time&amp;quot; searching without relying on filesystem semantics&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-710&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I hit this bug: on Windows&lt;br/&gt;
only, when SegmentReader.setNorm is called, but separate norms&lt;br/&gt;
(_X_N.sY) had already been previously saved, then, on closing the&lt;br/&gt;
reader, we will write the next gen separate norm file correctly&lt;br/&gt;
(_X_N+1.sY) but fail to delete the current one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s quite minor because the next writer to touch the index will&lt;br/&gt;
remove the stale file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because the Norm class still holds the IndexInput open when&lt;br/&gt;
the reader commits.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="12364024">LUCENE-820</key>
            <summary>SegmentReader.setNorm can fail to remove separate norms file, on Windows</summary>
